The number of protons in half the body mass  

\[
m_{\text{p}} = \frac{62\ \text{kg}}{2}=31\ \text{kg}
\]

\[
N = \frac{m_{\text{p}}}{m_{\text{proton}}}
   = \frac{31\ \text{kg}}{1.6726\times10^{-27}\ \text{kg}}
   \approx 1.85\times10^{28}\ \text{protons}
\]

Half‑life of a proton  

\[
T_{1/2}=10^{33}\ \text{yr}
\]

Decay constant  

\[
\lambda = \frac{\ln 2}{T_{1/2}}
        = \frac{0.693}{10^{33}\ \text{yr}}
        \approx 6.93\times10^{-34}\ \text{yr}^{-1}
\]

Activity (decays per year)  

\[
A_{\text{yr}} = \lambda N
               \approx 6.93\times10^{-34}\times1.85\times10^{28}
               \approx 1.28\times10^{-5}\ \text{decays/yr}
\]

Decays per day  

\[
A_{\text{day}} = \frac{A_{\text{yr}}}{365}
                \approx \frac{1.28\times10^{-5}}{365}
                \approx 3.5\times10^{-8}\ \text{decays/day}
\]

