For the bridge to be balanced the potentials at the two mid‑nodes must be equal, i.e.  

\[
V_A = V_B \;\Longrightarrow\; \frac{C_1}{C_2}= \frac{C_3}{C_4}
\]

Hence  

\[
C_2 = C_1\;\frac{C_4}{C_3}
\]

Substituting the given capacitances from the diagram  

\[
C_1 = 2\;\mu\text{F},\qquad C_3 = 4\;\mu\text{F},\qquad C_4 = 6\;\mu\text{F}
\]

\[
