The resistance of the cylindrical shell is  

\[
R = \rho \frac{L}{A}
     = \rho \frac{L}{\pi\left(R_o^{2}-R_i^{2}\right)}
\]

\[
\begin{aligned}
R_i &= 0.2\;\text{mm}=2.0\times10^{-4}\,\text{m}\\
R_o &= 0.3\;\text{mm}=3.0\times10^{-4}\,\text{m}\\
L   &= 0.9\;\text{mm}=9.0\times10^{-4}\,\text{m}\\[4pt]
A   &= \pi\big[(3.0\times10^{-4})^{2}-(2.0\times10^{-4})^{2}\big]
     = \pi\,(9-4)\times10^{-8}
     = 5\pi\times10^{-8}\,\text{m}^2\\[4pt]
R   &= \frac{3.5\times10^{-5}\,\Omega\!\cdot\!m \times 9.0\times10^{-4}\,m}
           {5\pi\times10^{-8}\,m^{2}}
     = \frac{3.15}{5\pi}\;\Omega
     \approx 0.2005\;\Omega
\end{aligned}
\]

#### 0.2005

The time after the aircraft passes directly overhead before the sonic boom is heard is  

\[
t = \frac{h}{c}\sqrt{1-\frac{1}{M^{2}}}
\]

where  

* \(h = 8000\ \text{m}\) (altitude)  
* \(c = 340\ \text{m/s}\) (speed of sound at that altitude)  
* \(M = 1.75\) (Mach number).

\[
\begin{aligned}
\sqrt{1-\frac{1}{M^{2}}} &= \sqrt{1-\frac{1}{1.75^{2}}}
= \sqrt{1-\frac{1}{3.0625}}
= \sqrt{0.6734694}
\approx 0.8207 \\[4pt]
t &= \frac{8000}{340}\times 0.8207
\approx 19.3\ \text{s}
\end{aligned}
\]

Rounded to the nearest integer, the delay is **19 seconds**.

